          "body": "The chapter — and the book — closes with a wisdom verse so distinctive it has often been read as a later editorial seal. *Whoever is wise, let him understand these things; whoever is discerning, let him know them. For the ways of the LORD are right, and the righteous will walk in them, but transgressors will stumble in them.* The verse turns the whole book into a fork in the road. The same *ways* (*derekh*) — Yahweh's revealed paths — heal the righteous and trip the rebellious. The diagnosis (*stumble*, *kashal*) bookends the chapter: Israel *stumbled by iniquity* in 14:1; transgressors *stumble in the ways of the LORD* in 14:9. The path that produces fall and the path that produces flourishing is one path. The variable is the heart that walks it."
